  <original-body>The &quot;automagic&quot; timezone conversion fails when you assign nil to a timezone aware attribute, for example:

&lt;code&gt;some_model.created_at = nil&lt;/code&gt;

And got an ugly &quot;TypeError: can't dup NilClass&quot;. I made an awesome and creative fix, check if the argument is nil =)

I also add a test so this will not append again.

Regards.</original-body>
